Fe3O4 is a typical magnetic iron oxide with a cubic inverse spinel structure in which oxygen forms a face-centered cubic close packing. Some of the Fe3+ occupy 1/8th of interstitial tetrahedral while equal amounts of Fe3+ and Fe2+ fill half of the available octahedral sites [48, 49] in the space group Fd3m¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
