				\begin{document}$$Fd3\bar{m}$$\end{document} with 0.8394 nm as lattice parameter. The conduction and the magnetism properties are mainly due to the distribution of these iron ions. Indeed, the electron spins of the Fe2+ and Fe3+ in the octahedral sites are coupled while the spins of the Fe3+ in the tetrahedral sites are anti-parallel coupled to those in octahedral sites. As the magnetic moments of the Fe3+ and Fe2+ are 5 and 4 Bohr magneton respectively, it results a magnetic moment equal to (→5←4←5) = 4 Bohr magneton (Fig. 4). This net effect is that the magnetic contributions of both sets are not balanced and it raises a permanent magnetism.Fig. 4
